{"key":"processedPost-6605097","value":{"id":6605097,"first":6604412,"last":6606946,"when":1172334997,"utime":"02/24/07 06:36 PM","content":"If you're doing pf tek, steam sterilization in a pot is just as effective because rice doesn't harbor bacterial endospores.  The important thing is not to start your timer until steam is escaping from under the lid of the pot.  From that time, which is about ten minutes after the water begins to boil, allow a full hour, then turn off the stove.  Allow the jars to sit in the pot with the lid on until cool.<br />RR","title":"Re: Much difference in success between pot and pressure cooker?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}